<br>
If you have spent the time collecting every item for the combine, then in your mind you have done all the work, and trader x just needs to hit combine.   How hard could it be for them really?  He/she would just have to be a generous person.  If they want to make the money they can farm the items themselves.<br>
<br>
But if you're the trader, you have spent tons of plat to cap out some trading skill.  When someone comes up and asks for a combine, thinking they did all the work - they really didn't, because to get this item there has to be a combine which requires many tedious hours of practice and farming.<br>
<br>
Its just a small summary of how i look at it anyways.<br>
<br>
I can't say I know how it feels to be able to make decent stuff (i think i stopped at banded with blacksmithing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) so I don't know what side I would take if I GMed something.  If it was something that is worth a fairly hefty ammount that I was planning to sell, I would be happy to give 1/2 the profit to the trader, but thats just me.<br>
