<br>
Well, i'm 250 in every tradeskill, yes it takes a long long time, and a lot of damned money to master a tradeskill, a LOT of time, and a LOT of money to master a tradeskill.<br>
<br>
I dont know anyone who macro's tradeskills, period.  It's the exception, not the norm to be a macro combiner.  If you think all the tradeskillers got to 250 easily, cheaply, and by doing no work but watching TV, come back when you can show me your 7 GM items and still say the same thing with a straight face.<br>
<br>
People do pay jack @#%$ for combines normally and yeah, it is a bit annoying when they resale stuff and make a frigging gold mine by buying stuff in baz and coming to you for combines.  I had this problem when I started doing combines too, but there are solutions.<br>
<br>
Someone will come to you, and they will want a combine, STRAIGHT AWAY assume they are going to turn to bazaar and sell it, as 99 % of combines will be sold in baz almost instantly.<br>
<br>
Now, think to yourself, &quot;hmmmm, at what price would i be happy to let this guy use me as his cash cow&quot; then you /reply him with that price.  For Tae Ew combines my price is 500pp per combine, sucess or failure.  Now that may seem steep, but one of my regulars has made about 300K selling tae ew things, and he always comes back for more...<br>
<br>
My biggest problem with tradeskilling is gimps who cant read eqtraders, now, i know a lot of people will reply to this stating how complex the site is.  <br>
<br>
No, you are wrong.  <br>
You are so very very wrong.  <br>
No, information is not missing.<br>
<br>
I get maybe 50-100 tells a day asking for recipes, or people want combines that either<br>
<br>
a) dont know the recipe<br>
b) heard recipe from friend and got it wrong<br>
c) assume that i'm an enchanter, tinker, poison maker, alchemist rolled into one that can do every pre combine and imbue/enchant.<br>
<br>
Said people with broken recipes usually get pissy when I tell them to visit a website for information on thier own combine...... rather than *ME* going to the website for thier combine, and then relaying the information in tells.....<br>
<br>
Anyways, i'm done ranting, short of it is, if you're not happy combining for peanuts, learn to tell em to shove it, no rules saying that you HAVE to max this tradeskill and HAVE to combine it for people.<br>
