<br>
I was a GM and this is how I worked:  <br>
<br>
-Friends and guildies get combines for free as long as it's for personal use. <br>
-Others asking for simple items for which components could be bought, or are trivial under 200 - charge peanuts...anybody can make those.<br>
-Items trivial 250+, bring me twice the components per attempt or I won't do it at all.<br>
<br>
Most GM skillers spent the time and effort you lazy assh*les won't so they could turn in a bit of a profit.  You don't do it to make others use your skill.  Very few will GM smithing or tailoring just for the hell of it.  It is too much of an investment... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hildie>Hildie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/10/03 10:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3159.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Own View</span><hr size=1> I do valor ring combines free for my guildies and friends when I know they are are going to use it personally.  I have no problem with that.  There is even a little guild fund of talons, raw diamonds, and bricks of valorium so that all the person really needs to give me is the liquid and either 2 sapphires or 210pp.  I stop what I'm doing quite frequently to run all over and do precombines and make mana vials and get buffed and do the combine.<br>
<br>
I say all this to show that I'm not just some greedy GM who wants to make a profit no matter what.<br>
<br>
That being said, I got a tell the other day from someone who wanted me to make 3 valor rings.  Now, with 3 rings, someone is making a profit.  This is not personal use.  He is making plat.  And yet he was affronted that I would dare ask a service fee for my time (he wasn't even going to come to me, I was supposed to go to him.)  After all, it was just a click of a button, and his argument was that I would have GMd the skill whether or not he asked me to click &quot;combine.&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm afraid I threw a bit of a tantrum.<br>
<br>
It is my belief that we all have different skills to contribute to our game. Some buff, some rez, some tradeskill, etc.  What you charge for those services is entirely up to the person.  You cant tell me &quot;I always sow people for free so you should do these combines for free.&quot;  That's wonderful you sow people (or rez people, or buff them, or whatever.)  I'm delighted you help people.  I help people for free too, in other ways.<br>
<br>
You make your plat in different ways.  Apparently, you like to spend your time to farm stuff and sell it.  That's perfectly OK.  I don't have time to farm like that.  Instead, I will take your parts and combine them into something you can sell at a higher price.  I don't ask for unreasonable compensation, I'm not even asking for half.  Just a little something that says you appreciate my efforts.<br>
<br>
You see how nicely that would work out?  You make plat, I make plat, and we are both doing our own thing in the game, helping each other out, and everyone's happy.  Just because I wont do it for free doesn't mean I'm not a nice person.  You have a friend that does it for free?  Fine, then wait for them to come online.  Doesn't hurt my feelings a bit.  I have another 40 stacks of celestial essence I need to make anyway.<br>
<br>
I am not an NPC.  When you hail me, I do not say, &quot;Greetings.  I can [buff] you, [imbue gems], [enchant] items, or [combine] goods for you to sell.&quot;  I am a player just like you, and I happen to have taken a path you did not.  I enjoy it.  I enjoy helping people when I can.  I enjoy creating.  That does not mean I feel compelled to bend over without the benefit of vaseline.<br>
<br>
