<br>
Woman plans her future.  She decides that, to fulfill herself emotioally and to make a good living, she needs to go to school.  She goes to college and becomes a doctor.  She has a ridiculous number of expenses involved, and pays thousands and thousands of plat to get herself an education.  Now, with her doctoral trophy in hand, she sets up shop.  She enjoys helping the sick.  It makes her feel good.  She loves her job.  <br>
<br>
People come to her and say, &quot;I am sick, but I cannot pay.  You doctors are all rich anyway, you don't need my money.&quot;  Or perhaps someone says, &quot;You would have become a doctor even if I were not sick right now, and it won't cost you anything to sign this prescription.&quot;  What do you suppose she tells them?<br>
<br>
Of course there ARE doctors out there that open free clinics.  Just as there are tradeskillers that combine for free.  Ask your guildies.<br>
<br>
Before any of you start in on ripping this apart, no I am NOT suggesting tradeskillers are as noble and self sacrificing as doctors.  No I am NOT saying we spend years and years of hell in med school or doing internships.  It's an example.<br>
<br>
***insert shamless plug here****<br>
<br>
/join artisan is a tradeskill channel with tradeskillers of all kinds.  We have a few people coming in to ask questions, and we generally answer as thoroughly as we can.  We often do combines for people that drop by the channel for that reason, and the price is negotiated by the asker and the tradeskiller.  We do price checks on tradeskilled goods.  We can refer you to GM's that have allowed us to use their names if one is not in the channel at that time.  We're growing, and often have 10-15 people in at one time, with people dropping in all day.<br>
<br>
And, of course, we have a good time. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.familjenguild.com/dspMember.php?Name=Hildie"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.familjenguild.com/images/logo/hildie.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morloc>Morloc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:blue;'>Tavern Regular</span></span><br>  Posts: 481<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/10/03 3:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3159.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~lnalewajk/_images/Scrimm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: an analogy</span><hr size=1> <br>
